.TH "clk_hw_round_rate" 9 "clk_hw_round_rate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clk_hw_round_rate \- round the given rate for a hw clk
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" clk_hw_round_rate
.BI "(struct clk_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "unsigned long rate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
the hw clk for which we are rounding a rate
.IP "rate" 12
the rate which is to be rounded
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Takes in a rate as input and rounds it to a rate that the clk can actually
use.
.SH "CONTEXT"
prepare_lock must be held.
For clk providers to call from within clk_ops such as .round_rate,
\&.determine_rate.
.SH "RETURN"
returns rounded rate of hw clk if clk supports round_rate operation
else returns the parent rate.
